abstract: UTICA, N.Y., March 4.--Democratic Utica elects James S. Sherman (Rep.) Mayor by about 1,200 majority over Lewis H. Shattuck. The Mayor-elect is a son of Gen. Richard U. Sherman.

abstract: CINCINNATI, Ohio, March 13.--The leading inventors of the country have issued a call for a convention to take action to prevent pernicious legislation by Congress. abstract: NASHVILLE, Tenn., March 25.--Winnie Thompson and Lucy Sackers, both colored, residing in an alley between Summer and High streets, left their two children at home to-night with a lamp sitting near a bed.
